snippet.textDisplay:
Falun Gong practitioners in Japan participated in the 22nd annual Sobue Ginkgo Festival, November 23-24, 2019 in Inazawa. Located in Aichi Prefecture, Inazawa City has more than 10,000 ginkgo trees and is known as the “golden city.” The festival was held at the Sobue-Cho Gym.

The practitioners distributed fliers to passers-by and demonstrated the Falun Gong exercises at their booth. Visitors were happy to accept their beautiful handmade paper lotus flowers.
